   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1815_03_01_page01.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <name type="place" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/tgn/7001306"/>15 Baggot Street<lb/>
                        Dublin<lb/>
                  <date when="1815-03-01"/>March 01, 1815<lb/>
               </dateline>
               <salute> My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">Madam</persName>
                  <lb/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
                    Enclosed are two drafts amounting<lb/>
                    to £37 which I believe is the amount<lb/>
                    of my debt to you - I have received<lb/>
                    all your bills &amp; receipts &amp; I thank<lb/>
                    you for your kind punctuality<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> The box containing all our <choice>
                  <orig>trea<lb/>
                    sures</orig>
                  <reg>treasures</reg>
               </choice> has not yet arrived; but I have<lb/>
                    this very day heard that it was safe<lb/>
                    at <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/tgn/7013189">Holyhead</placeName> &amp; that it would be put<lb/>
                    on Board the Henrietta the 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. So that<lb/>
                    I trust it will soon be here &amp; we shall<lb/>
                    shine forth in the lace &amp; satin you<lb/>
                    have been so kind to cause for us -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I regret very much that we have<lb/>
                    now closed our concerns with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Miles</persName>
               <lb/>
                    but I trust that we shall not become<lb/>
                    strangers to each other - We depend upon<lb/>
                    your keeping your promise &amp; coming<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1815_03_01_page02.jpg"/>
                    next summer to <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/tgn/1042937">Edgeworth's Town</placeName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <closer> 
                 I am Dear Madam,<lb/>
                 Your obliged Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>I trust that if there is any thing<lb/>
                    remaining due to you my dear<lb/>
                    madam which is not included<lb/>
                    in your bills or accts you will<lb/>
                    let me know<lb/>
               </p>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1815_03_01_page03.jpg"/>
               <p>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GodlX1">Capt<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>. Godley's</persName> address<lb/>
                    in <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/tgn/7000198">India</placeName> - I have written<lb/>
                    to try to obtain the direction<lb/>
                        to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#McCaX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. M<hi rend="superscript">c</hi>Cann</persName> but fear it<lb/>
                    will be too late<lb/>
                    tell <persName>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Hu<unclear/>
                  </persName> ask for<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Miles</persName>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <!--You can include a <pb/> here, or inside the postScript.-->
